name: Lawar kambing Mang Raka Gianyar
address: Jl. Raya Tojan No.29, Blahbatuh, Kec. Blahbatuh, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80581, Indonesia
review 1: 1st time ever tried and it was recommended by my wife. It has similarities with the Java Madura style of satay that uses peanut sauce and curry, but it has the satay Lilit that is made from Goat meat, and the Lawar makes it different in variation of the cuisine.
review 2: Best KAMBING food in town. Local and traditional. The parking-man not too good but dont worry. The price look so expensive but you must try. No pork, halal food but cooked by balinese. Must try
review 3: Everything was Good, the place is quite comfortable, the food was delicious, but for the lawar, it should be even better. And the Gule is a bit less thick. Overall was worth it.
review 4: While most places serve pork lawar, this place serves lamb lawar. The lawar itself is a mix of vegetables and tendon. The soup is bright and spicy with tender meat (very fatty). The satay is alright, but served with sweet peanut sauce. The place is spacious and clean for a "warung".
review 5: Perfect Balinese lawar, delicious, not to spicy

name: Villa Dwipa by Ayu
address: Jl. Raya Tojan, Blahbatuh, Kec. Blahbatuh, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80581, Indonesia
review 1:
This place is like a dream come true !
Staying in this Bamboe villa gives you so much peace and relaxation where you feel yourself complete with nature.
You have alot of privacy here, very quiet and enough posibilities to find a spot for meditation.

The location is perfect when you want to visit other places. You can even rent a scooter if you want to.

Ayu, the host, is such a nice and kind women who makes the best breakfast with alot of variety.
She can guide you when you want to visit other places. Even her family will take care of you.

The villa is guarded 24/7 what gives you a really safe feeling.

Anyway … no doubt to stay in this villa.

Thank you so much Ayu… I will come back !!
